.TH ANIMUX 1 "July 5, 2026" "animux 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
animux \- browse and watch anime from your terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B animux
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIQUERY\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B animux
is a POSIX shell CLI/TUI for browsing and playing anime on macOS and Linux.
It supports English and Spanish subtitle modes. Internally, animux routes each
language to the best available source.
.PP
Source fallback order is:
.IP \(bu 2
Spanish subtitles: JKanime, AnimeFLV, AnimeFenix, TioAnime, AnimeAV1.
.IP \(bu 2
Spanish dub: MonosChinos, AnimeFLV, AnimeAV1.
.IP \(bu 2
English: AllAnime first, then Gogoanime when search or episode resolution fails.
.PP
The interactive main menu includes a personal anime library. It can save shows
for later, track watched episodes, mark completed or dropped shows, keep
favorites, and preview cover art. The existing ani-hsts history and Continue
watching flow remain available independently.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-continue
Continue watching from history.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-download
Download instead of playing.
.TP
.BR \-D ", " \-\-delete
Delete watch history.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-logview
Show logs.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-episode ", " \-r ", " \-\-range " " \fIEPISODE\fR"
Select one episode or an episode range.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show command help.
.TP
.BR \-L ", " \-\-language " " \fILANG\fR"
Select subtitle language: en or es.
.TP
.BR \-P ", " \-\-provider " " \fIPROVIDER\fR"
Advanced: force an internal provider. Usually not needed. Most users should use
.BR \-L " en"
or
.BR \-L " es"
instead.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quality " " \fIQUALITY\fR"
Set best, worst, 360, 480, 720, or 1080.
.TP
.BR \-S ", " \-\-select-nth " " \fIINDEX\fR"
Select the nth menu entry.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-syncplay
Play through Syncplay.
.TP
.BR \-U ", " \-\-update
Update the source script from the animux repository.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print the version.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-vlc
Use VLC as the player.
.TP
.BR \-\-dmenu
Use dmenu instead of fzf.
.TP
.BR \-\-dub
Use dubbed media where supported.
.TP
.BR \-\-exit-after-play
Exit after playback and return the player status.
.TP
.BR \-\-no-detach
Keep the player attached to the terminal.
.TP
.BR \-\-rofi
Use rofi instead of fzf.
.TP
.BR \-\-skip
Use ani-skip to skip intros with mpv.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The public configuration namespace is
.BR ANIMUX_* .
The corresponding legacy
.B ANI_CLI_*
names remain supported as fallbacks.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_PROVIDER
Advanced internal provider override: auto, allanime, or jkanime.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_CACHE
Set to 0 to bypass reading and writing cached search results and episode lists.
The legacy ANI_CLI_CACHE variable is supported as a fallback. Playback URLs,
resolved embeds, and direct streams are never cached.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_PLAYER
Player command or mode. Common values include mpv, vlc, debug, and download.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_HIST_DIR
Watch-history directory. The default is
.IR $XDG_STATE_HOME/animux ,
or
.IR $HOME/.local/state/animux .
.TP
.B ANIMUX_LIBRARY_FILE
Personal-library JSON file. The default is
.IR $XDG_STATE_HOME/animux/library.json ,
or
.IR $HOME/.local/state/animux/library.json .
.TP
.B ANIMUX_LIBRARY_ART
Set to 0 to disable cover art in library views. ANIMUX_EPISODE_ART=0 also
disables library art.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_LIBEXEC_DIR
Directory containing anime-extractor, extractor.py, and the extractors Python
package.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_SHARE_DIR
Directory containing bundled art assets.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_BUILTIN_ART
Explicit path to menuPixelArt.txt.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_ASCII_ART
Explicit path to a single ASCII art file. When set, this overrides the random
collection.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_ASCII_ART_DIR
Directory containing random ASCII art files for the main menu.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_RANDOM_ASCII_ART
Set to 0 to disable random ASCII art and use the bundled asciiArt.txt fallback.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_NO_HEADER
Set to 1 to hide the command header.
.TP
.B ANIMUX_HEADER
Set to 0 to hide the command header.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_STATE_HOME/animux/ani-hsts
Watch history.
.TP
.I $XDG_STATE_HOME/animux/library.json
Personal anime library. This file is separate from ani-hsts and is replaced
atomically after successful updates.
.TP
.I $XDG_CACHE_HOME/animux
Cached art and metadata; when XDG_CACHE_HOME is unset, the location is
.IR $HOME/.cache/animux .
Search results are stored below
.I search/
for 6 hours, and episode lists below
.I episodes/
for 24 hours.
.TP
.I $PREFIX/share/animux/ascii/*.txt
Random ASCII art collection used by the main menu.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
animux
animux -L es "one piece"
animux -L en "demon slayer"
animux -c
animux -q 720p "frieren"
anime-extractor search --lang es "frieren"
anime-extractor search --lang es --dub "dragon ball"
anime-extractor search --lang en "solo leveling"
.fi
.SS Advanced provider override
Most users should not need this because animux selects an internal source from
the requested subtitle language.
.nf
animux -P allanime -L en "frieren"
animux -P jkanime -L es "one piece"
.fi
